io.codecastle.scriptorium.json

Class JsonValue<P>

  • Object
    • JsonValue<P>
  • Type Parameters:
    P - the type of the containing JsonArray or JsonObject
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    FluentAppendable<JsonValue<P>>, FluentNode<P>, Inscribable<JsonAppendable<?>,JsonValue<P>>, JsonAppendable<JsonValue<P>>, Closeable, Appendable, AutoCloseable

    public final class JsonValue<P>
extends Object
implements FluentNode<P>
    Represents a JSON string literal currently being output within a containing JsonArray or JsonObject.
    See Also:
    JsonArray.element(), JsonKey.value()

        Description copied from interface: JsonAppendable
        Appends the specified subsequence of the provided CharSequence and returns this object.

        The provided characters will be escaped.

        This method differs from Appendable.append(CharSequence, int, int): if the provided sequence is null or if start is less than zero or end is less than or equal to start, this method has no effect.

      • inscribe

        public <T extends FluentNode<THIS>> T inscribe(IOFunction<? super THIS,T> function)
                                        throws IOException
        Description copied from interface: io.codecastle.scriptorium.Inscribable
        Inscribes another FluentNode in this object, and returns it.

        This method calls the provided function, passing this object as the input, and returns the output.

        When the FluentNode.then() method of the returned node is called, this object will be returned.

        When this object or a parent object is closed, the FluentNode returned by this method will also be closed if it has not already been.
